      <selectionEntries>
        <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Tech-Priest" hidden="false" id="1c07-b463-3797-7488">
          <profiles>
            <profile name="Maintenance Liturgy" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="3216-2bfa-e100-66b5">
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">After this unit’s Move step, select a friendly vehicle unit within 6” of this unit. The selected unit Repairs D3+1 and gains the following ability:


Surging Motive Force: For each attack made for this unit, add 1 to the Hit Roll of that attack. After this unit’s Attacks step, it loses this ability.</characteristic>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
            <profile name="Resurging Machine" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="6065-4257-1610-1eee">
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">After this unit uses its Mendicant&apos;s Sacrament ability, the selected unit gains +X M until the End step, where X is equal to the Repair X.</characteristic>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
            <profile name="Predictive Algorithms" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="0d91-daf1-3c63-ffdf">
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">While this unit is within 1” of one or more of your other units, for each attack that targets this unit, the Saving Throw of that attack is improved by 1.</characteristic>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
            <profile name="Soothing Commune" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="eaa0-7f59-1cbc-0585">
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">For each Explode Roll made for any friendly vehicle within 9” of this unit, you may reroll the result.</characteristic>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
          </profiles>
          <constraints>
            <constraint type="min" value="1" field="selections" scope="parent" shared="true" id="86f6-f0f1-95c7-e0d6-min" includeChildSelections="false"/>
            <constraint type="max" value="1" field="selections" scope="parent" shared="true" id="86f6-f0f1-95c7-e0d6-max" includeChildSelections="false"/>
          </constraints>
